Try `&lt;constant name=&quot;struts.patternMatcher&quot; value=&quot;regex&quot;/&gt;` the only viable matcher for the constants above. This is usually used with advanced wildcards mode, explained [here][1]. 

&gt;Advanced Wildcards
&gt;From 2.1.9+ regular expressions can be defined defined in the action name. To use this form of wild card, the following constants must be set:
```xml
&lt;constant name=&quot;struts.enable.SlashesInActionNames&quot; value=&quot;true&quot;/&gt;
&lt;constant name=&quot;struts.mapper.alwaysSelectFullNamespace&quot; value=&quot;false&quot;/&gt;
&lt;constant name=&quot;struts.patternMatcher&quot; value=&quot;regex&quot; /&gt;
```
The URL splitted into namespace `/` and action name `partner/partnerName`. The last matches a pattern compiled from the name in the action config using a wildcard mapper, which is a default mapper.


  [1]: https://struts.apache.org/core-developers/wildcard-mappings#advanced-wildcards

